#how to run
#Install Python 3.9+ (optionally create a virtual env), open a terminal in your project folder, save the code I shared as supply_chain_optimization.py, then install dependencies with pip install pandas numpy scikit-learn pulp matplotlib and run python supply_chain_optimization.py; the script will auto-generate a realistic synthetic dataset, train a demand-forecast model, optimize inventory via linear programming, and build delivery routes, saving everything in the output/ folder (sales_history.csv, forecast_horizon.csv, inventory_plan.csv, routes.json, routes_plot.png, forecast_example.png, summary.json)â€”just open those files to inspect results; if you prefer real data, replace the generated CSVs in output/ with your own (same columns) and re-run to produce a portfolio-ready pipeline end-to-end.
